dataqual.logic: This parcel layer contains discrete, non-overlapping polygons for each property. Adjacent polygons with common ownership and a single tax record have been retained in the "OthLeg" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer, and dissolved into single parcels in this TaxPar layer. Some non-adjacent parcels may be represented by multi-part polygons where they share common ownership and a single tax record. Public rights-of-way (ROWs) exist as polygons, not null space. Linework associated with private ROWs are retained in the "OthLeg" layer. Water polygons also representing parcel boundaries have been retained in this TaxPar layer. Additional water features that are not considered parcel boundaries may have been placed in the "Misc" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer. Easements and other similar non-fee taxable boundaries exist in the "OthLeg" layer, not the TaxPar layer. Based on municipality and/or record information, some TaxPar layer POLY_TYPE='ROW' violate v2.1 of the MassGIS Standard in that they are not always 'cut' by TaxPar layer POLY_TYPE = 'RAIL_ROW'. This is a MassGIS approved variation of the standard.

overview.dsoverv: M286TaxPar represents a version of digital municipal parcels for the community of Stow that is considered ‘level 3’ compliant per the specifications outlined in the MassGIS Standard for Digital Parcel Files. Its features can be linked in a GIS or database environment to a set of standardized assessing attributes in the table M286Assess by using the unique identifying values in the LOC_ID field. This data is also intended to be used in conjunction with associated (and optional) features in the ancillary data layers M286OthLeg and M286Misc. As one of the data sets identified by Massachusetts’ Strategic Plan for Spatial Data Infrastructure (http:/ /www.mass.gov/mgis/stratplan.html), this data enters the public domain as a valuable resource for mapping, planning, and analysis at all levels of government as well as the private sector.

dataIdInfo.idAbs: Assessor's parcel data set for the Town of Stow updated pursuant to the tax situs date of January 1, 2025. These data are developed from existing digital data using CADD and GIS software tools. Parcel geometry and attribute data are updated to January 1, 2025. The related CAMA data are current to June 17, 2025. The parcel boundaries and other features are updated based on instruments of record including property deeds and recorded boundary survey and subdivision plans. Other source materials include right-of-way plans, flood plain studies, and historical tax maps dating back to 1971. Recent updates have been performed using MassGIS ortho-imagery current to 2019 and 2021 as base layers.
dataIdInfo.idCredit: Town of Stow, Board of Assessors working with various vendors. Original source materials were compiled in 1971 by John E. O'Donnell & Associates (Auburn, ME). Hardcopy maps were digitized in 1998 by Aerial Survey and Photo, Inc (Norridgewock, ME). Parcel data were upgraded in 2017 by CAI Technologies (Littleton, NH). Further updates in 2017 and 2018 were performed by Hilltop Northeast Enterprises (Brimfield, MA) and more recent updates since 2019 have been performed by Robert Rogers - Cadastral Services (Farmington Falls, ME).
